const becauseTheyStartWithWhy = `<p>Salt Essential IT (Pty) Ltd does not rest on its laurels. The company – celebrating its 25th birthday in March – has, yet again, made history by obliterating its own PMR.africa Diamond Arrow Awards winning streak.</p><p>The company has now been awarded three awards consecutively for four (4!) years. The award categories in which Salt has clinched the first spot and the coveted Diamond Arrow Awards are Cloud Service Providers, Data Centres, and IT Consulting Companies. No ICT company in the history of the business journal has even come close to this achievement. The 2022 awards bring Salt’s Diamond Arrow Awards tally to 20 in 10 years.&nbsp;</p><p>When the managing director, Sonja Coetzer is asked, “How do you do it?”, she responds with “It is never the how, it is always the why. ”</p><p>She continues, “Salt is honoured that our dedication to our clients through our client centric approach to delivery sees us winning these prestigious awards.Winning these awards 4 times in a row is truly a reason to celebrate.” “As we cannot enter, nominate or rate ourselves in this research, we are appreciative of the votes we receive, it makes the <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Why</span> so much &nbsp;more worth it! The <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Why</span> we are in business, is very important to us –we are in business to implement technology that optimises business and empowers people to effectively operate in a secure, productive, and sustainable manner .”</p><p>Coetzer explains that every Saltie embraces our mission and vision that is a living embodiment of our daily pursuit to deliver on our commitments.&nbsp; Salt’s evolution of the past 25 years has seen the company and its employees leading the market with solutions that disrupts industries in the Namibian market. Salt believes that enabled, empowered, and future-fit people are the most important asset a business can have to survive, grow and prosper.</p><p>“This is why we are in business. From inception we worked towards delivering technology that moved from being an architecture and systems provider to a partnership-based, human-centric business optimisation provider. And over the last 15 years, we’ve been continuously reinventing and refining this Why.”</p><p>“It is amazingly hard sometimes and we are not always successful the first time we try new technologies. Fortunately for our customers, by the time we recommend and implement tech in their space, they know we’ve thoroughly analysed and tested it, and we will do extraordinary effort to empower the people that will ultimately use it.”</p><p>Months before Covid-lockdowns in 2020, Salt was moving 4 thousand of users to cloud-computing services, but if ever Salt proved their fixation on future fitness, this was it. The company now serves 270 000 cloud-users at their customers across Namibia.</p><p>“Salt is a true team effort, and like most things, when the collective comes together greatness are delivered. Every Saltie’s dedication, commitment, and die-hard tenacity towards living and breathing our values every day is what makes all the difference at every customer.”</p><p>“The people at Salt enables your people to enable your business. That is our number one priority. And that’s why we are here.”</p><h3> #futurefit #pmr #knowledge #awards</h3><figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="/Articles/Sonja1.jpg" alt="" width="146" height="146"></figure><p>Sonja Coetzer - Managing Director</p>`;

// ======================================================================
// Bits to Bliss: Navigating the AI Frontier Part 2
// Slug: bits-to-bliss-navigating-the-ai-frontier-part-2
// ======================================================================
const bitsToBlissNavigatingTheAiFrontierPart2 = `<p>Do I get to say, I love Artificial Intelligence again,(as mentioned in the automation blog), or would it be too repetitive? Artificial Intelligence bots have become a business need and can no longer be seen as just a commodity. Bots can serve your business in many ways, including finding the right contact person for the customer query, bringing data together to improve information transparency and clarity, and so much more.</p><p>Have you ever visited a really big website and found yourself to be drilling through, what feels like, endless links and pages and information only to feel more perplexed and overwhelmed than anything? </p><p>How about finding the right contact information to serve your query? Calling the switchboard, only to be redirected throughout the building without relevant assistance? It is not only frustrating, (and know that you are not alone), but it is also time consuming, and quite possibly leaves you more upset than satisfied. This is but one area where an Artificial intelligence (AI) bot can serve not just you, but your business as a whole.</p><p>Allow me to share ChatGPT’s version on the topic briefly outlining the pro’s and cons of Artificial intelligence bots, who also supplied a link to the entire source for you to read should you so wish <a href="https://www.tidio.com/blog/ai-chatbot/">22 Best AI Chatbots for 2023: ChatGPT &amp; Alternatives (tidio.com)</a></p><p><em>Artificial intelligence (AI) bots are becoming increasingly popular on websites as businesses look for ways to improve customer service and engagement. AI bots can help businesses automate tasks, provide 24/7 support, and improve the overall customer experience. Here are some of the key benefits of adding an AI bot to your website:</em></p><ul><li><strong><em>Improved customer service:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;AI bots can provide customers with instant support, answering their questions and resolving issues quickly.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Increased efficiency:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;AI bots can perform tasks faster and more efficiently than humans, freeing up time for employees to focus on more complex tasks.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Cost savings:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;By automating certain tasks, businesses can save money on labor costs.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Personalization:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;AI bots can use data to personalize the customer experience, providing tailored recommendations and content.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Increased engagement:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;AI bots can engage customers in conversation, providing a more interactive experience.</em></li></ul><p><em>However, there are also some potential drawbacks to consider when adding an AI bot to your website:</em></p><ul><li><strong><em>Lack of human touch:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;Some customers may prefer interacting with a human representative rather than a bot.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Technical issues:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;AI bots may encounter technical issues that require human intervention to resolve.</em></li> <li><strong><em>Data privacy concerns:</em></strong><em>&nbsp;Collecting and using customer data comes with privacy concerns that need to be addressed.</em></li></ul><p><em>In conclusion, adding an AI bot to your website can provide many benefits for your business. However, it is important to weigh the pros and cons and determine if it is the right choice for your specific needs.</em></p><p>Here is my, (no AI), conclusion:</p><p>Artificial intelligence Bots can become your online superhero and go-to for your clients when they visit your website. These bots can be an introvert’s best friend and at the same time empower the time focused client when they visit your website. For our customer centric Salty innovation house, we have Zolt, who is a perfect example of an Artificial Intelligence Bot built specifically to serve our business environment and services. Zolt does not operate outside of the set parameters, this brings ethical AI back into our conversation where it should be, and again brings the business enabling tool to top of mind.</p><h3> #AI #algorithm #websites</h3><figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="/Articles/jayleeventer.png" alt="" style="width:155px;height:155px" width="155" height="155"></figure><p>Jaylee Venter - Customer Technical Liaison</p>`;

// ======================================================================
// Bits to Bliss: Navigating the AI Frontier
// Slug: bits-to-bliss-navigating-the-ai-frontier
// ======================================================================
const bitsToBlissNavigatingTheAiFrontier = `<p>Part 1</p><p>I love artificial intelligence simply because of the amazing things that it can do for people and businesses at large. Of course, being hands on in the world of Artificial intelligence I leveraged the AI offered by ChatGPT to assist me with this blog, which I reviewed and credit checked as far as humanly possible prior to posting the content. The importance of monitoring, credit checking and more by developers and users throughout the world cannot be understated and forever lingers in the back of my mind as someone who advocates ethical artificial intelligence.</p><p>Automation is one of my favorite forms of artificial intelligence, and there are many, but automation is a true business enabler. Taking away mundane everyday tasks so that we can better use the time available to us in a working day. Sending weekly reports via email could take up to 1 hour to send, why not automate it? Get back a vital hour of your day so that you may shift your focus to more important tasks, and why not? Here, in this business scenario, artificial intelligence is your best friend, not just to you, but also to the business.</p><p>Here is a blog on pro’s and cons of Artificial intelligence automation written by ChatGPT, who also supplied a link to the entire source for you to read should you so wish, <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/qai/2022/12/01/the-pros-and-cons-of-artificial-intelligence/">The Pros And Cons Of Artificial Intelligence (forbes.com)</a>:</p><p><em>Artificial intelligence (AI) is a powerful technology that has the potential to revolutionize the way we live and work. However, like any new technology, it has its pros and cons. In this blog post, we will explore some of the key advantages and disadvantages of AI automation.</em></p><p><strong><em>Pros:</em></strong><em></em></p><ul><li><em>Fewer errors: AI can help reduce errors in tasks that are repetitive or require a high degree of accuracy.</em></li> <li><em>Increased efficiency: AI can perform tasks faster and more efficiently than humans.</em></li> <li><em>Cost savings: By automating certain tasks, businesses can save money on labor costs.</em></li> <li><em>Improved decision-making: AI can analyze large amounts of data quickly and accurately, helping businesses make better decisions.</em></li> <li><em>Enhanced customer experience: AI-powered chatbots and virtual assistants can provide customers with 24/7 support.</em></li></ul><p><strong><em>Cons:</em></strong><em></em></p><ul><li><em>Job displacement: As AI becomes more prevalent, some jobs may become obsolete.</em></li> <li><em>Lack of creativity: AI is not capable of creative thinking or innovation.</em></li> <li><em>Security risks: As AI becomes more sophisticated, it may become more difficult to secure against cyber threats.</em></li> <li><em>Bias: AI algorithms may be biased based on the data they are trained on.</em></li> <li><em>Dependence on technology: As we become more reliant on AI, we may lose some of our ability to perform tasks without it.</em></li></ul><p><em>In conclusion, while AI automation has many benefits, it also has its drawbacks. It is up to businesses and individuals to weigh the pros and cons and determine how best to incorporate this technology into their lives and work.</em></p><p>Here is my, (no AI), conclusion:</p><p>Artificial intelligence must be viewed, not as an enemy to mankind, but as a tool to be used for enablement. We fear what we do not understand and thus, we must ensure that we empower ourselves to better understand the Artificial Intelligence available to us today in the world. It is also important to Support the initiatives that focus on ethical AI as this will establish the foundational and vital “moral compass” and “does and don’ts” that serves not just businesses worldwide, but mankind as a whole.</p><h3> #automation #futurefit #smartwebsites</h3><figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="/Articles/jayleeventer.png" alt="" style="width:155px;height:155px" width="155" height="155"></figure><p>Jaylee Venter - Customer Technical Liaison</p>`;

// ======================================================================
// Can Technology Bring Government and Citizens Closer?
// Slug: can-technology-bring-government-and-citizens-closer
// ======================================================================
const canTechnologyBringGovernmentAndCitizensCloser = `<p>In all honesty, I do not want to be a President in this day and age, nor would I like to be a Minister or a member of parliament.</p><p>Governments and Presidents are constantly under fire, dissatisfied citizens of the world are on the increase, whether the topics are jobs, food, homes, education, health, or infrastructure.</p><p>The disconnect is huge, governments and Presidents believe that they are doing their best, yet, the question is, is that what the citizens want? Also, how do they cater for it all with limited budgets, high demands, and endless expectations?</p><p>Citizens want food on the table, a roof over their heads, well-maintained infrastructure, quality education, and health care, and above all jobs to provide for their families. Rather a tall order, come to think of it.</p><p>Is technology the answer, and if so, how can governments and Presidents leverage technology to deliver on the need for immediate gratification whilst improving on the conditions of satisfaction?</p><p>On the other hand, do governments know what it is that their citizens want? Are they connected to those they have been elected by to serve? Are they optimising service delivery through digitisation and quick access? Are they creating trust through transparency? Is there a strategy empowered by a fair and sufficient budget? Does information and communication technology form part of this?</p><p>Information Technology can enable a policy decision taken by government to be quickly executed and implemented at multiple locations, across the length and breadth of the country.</p><p>According to a news article on <em>drishti, </em>technology can be used to bring about e-Legislature, strengthen parliamentary committees, virtual judiciary, promote participative democracy, implement good governance, achieving sustainable development goals. All this through technology.</p><p>Governments can no longer wait for perfect and expensive solutions, they need to adopt available working ICT solutions today, and work together with the citizens to refine and improve the delivery of key services for economic prosperity and political stability. Once governments understand the intelligence and functionality in their existing procured technologies, they will understand how they can start rolling out various e-Services today.</p><p>Technology holds the key to seating government and citizens around the same dinner table to understand and attain common goals and objectives. It also enables transparency through the government’s ability to communicate directly with the citizens and eliminate disinformation and disconnection. It becomes easier for citizens to hold government accountable for their commitments to improve, uplift, develop and grow a country as a whole.</p><p>In conclusion, when governments embrace transparent technology, citizens are able to prosper.</p><figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="150" height="150" src="/Articles/Salt-ChristopherSwart.jpg" alt="Christopher Swart"></figure><p><em> Author: Christopher Swart - Commercial Expansion Account Manager @ Salt</em></p>`;

